(50, 'Key Qs: 1. Meesho learnings 1. What was the fist company - Worlzen - learnings? 1. What was 2nd company - Rotee - learnings? 1. How did LT happen? 1. Learnings from Valmo? 1. Learnings from Meesho Grocery? 1. Current state 1. Why Parag? 1. Why do concierge? 1. What is the wedge? 1. How to solve long tail supply? 1. What is the differentiation in the approach? 1. ICP 1. Monetization
RM reflections - Maybe: ++ Structured - clarity on NSM - drilled in from Meesho ++ Product mind ++ Reasonably outside in - studied Crew, interviewed Faff users ++ Highest level of FMF for orchestration play given Valmo +? Interesting wedge - non-knowledge work | outside the house tasks | chottu is the gig worker +? Some exposure to managing offline field Ops but should probe L1 | Built Valmo partner app & onboarded 2L+ partners | Although I don’t think these guys can do it outside Meesho +? When probed, very sharp learnings on founder journey in context of Meesho ?? Wants to do Ops light / orchestration - digitization of supply v/s owning supply || Feel pattern match from Meesho (8.5 Lakh sellers online) || Supply backwards approach ?? Commercial skills remain a question mark | “5% of supply charges” What would change my views: - Reflect on this approach - V/s other founders we have met? - Quality of L1s to manage Ops
RM notes: - Lucknow born - BTech Marine BITS 2014 - Raising $2M to $3M - $500K commitment - Vidit participation convo TBD Cash POV - This is Task Rabbit like play from USA'),
(52, 'Company Snapshot: Problem & solution Current tax filing journey is friction-prone, manual, and error‑prone with late submissions and notices. AXO proposes proactive tax planning, integrated filing, and year‑round wealth optimisation, using automated data ingestion from AIS/Accounts Aggregator (AA)/eRI, continuous monitoring, and AI‑driven planning to turn tax compliance into a wealth management asset. Ideal customer profile and pricing Target segments and personas Early professional: simple filing; basic 80C deductions; MF/NPS suggestions; first‑time tax education. Mid‑career professional: regime selection; HRA/LTA, 80C/D; MF SIPs, NPS for tax saving; proactive planning. Senior professional: capital gains, ESOP/RSU, property income; quarterly advance tax; active portfolio management. Pricing model (current players’ bands) Low complexity (Salary/Single Form 16): ₹0–₹799 Mid complexity (F&O traders/crypto/freelancers): ₹2,500–₹4,500 High complexity (NRIs/foreign assets/audits): ₹7,500–₹15,000+ [Inference] Mass‑affluent segment targeted; ARPU uplift expected with wealth products and year‑round planning. Status of product & traction highlight Roadmap focuses on early adoption and scaling milestones; aims to reach significant user bases with annual targets: Target: 20k users by AY 2026‑27 Target: 100k users by AY 2027‑28 Target: 400k users by AY 2028‑29 Target: 800k users by AY 2029‑30 Funding request: ~$3 million to launch, iterate, and reach Series A readiness [Data source: Road...'),
